FBIS4-1391 "drafr082_c_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-082 Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Police Question Suspect Police Question Suspect MB2704074994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0736 GMT 27 Apr 94 MB2704074994 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] Johannesburg April 27 SAPA -- Police were questioning a suspect who matched the description of a white man seen running away from a car shortly before Jan Smuts Airport was rocked by a powerful car bomb on Wednesday. SAP [South African Police] spokesman Capt Wikus Webber said the suspect had been driving a white Toyota. He was fairly tall and had long brown hair. Police confirmed there had been no deaths as a result of the blast but said two injured people were in a serious condition. Police confirmed the blast had been a car bomb. Airport workers were still cleaning up debris -- mostly shattered glass -- at 9.30AM after the 7.15AM blast. At least 18 people were injured in the blast.
